Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.65,0:00:10.86,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,In order to restore my faith in this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.73,0:00:13.99,club,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,400)\an9}Let's start a competitive karuta club!\NPlease come see Ayase Chihaya in class 1-2!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.36,0:00:26.47,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,I have learned to both love \Nand hate my fellow man
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.50,0:00:32.75,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,Swift waters parted by the jagged rocks
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.75,0:00:35.49,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,are joined at river's end
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.23,0:00:57.75,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,Waves creep closer to the Suminoe shore...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.28,0:01:03.19,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,in my dreams, I creep closer to you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.04,0:01:11.49,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,Like the sound...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.55,0:01:18.55,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,After many, many years...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.55,0:01:21.06,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,Look for the sound...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.51,0:01:27.44,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I can't beat Chihaya to the \Nfirst-syllable cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.50,0:01:30.23,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Reassess the situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.85,0:01:34.85,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,"Would this" was already read so \NI can take "Would the" on the "Would."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.85,0:01:39.52,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,"My only thought as I" and "My only thought as the" \Nare both still in play, so I'll have to be careful there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.52,0:01:43.20,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,"So the flower petals" was already read, \Nso I can take "So the flower has" after "flower."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.20,0:01:45.61,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,"Though my" was already read,\Nso I can take "Though I" after "Though."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.61,0:01:50.66,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,For "While it pains", "While it may" was read, \Nbut "While it brings" wasn't, so I'll have to pay attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.66,0:01:55.05,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,For "The hazy early morning light", \N"The hazy early morning mist" was already read,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.05,0:01:57.30,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,so on "The hazy", I'll move towards \N"The hazy field" on the opponent's side.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.30,0:01:59.26,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,"In the" and "In order to" have already been read,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.26,0:02:00.89,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,so I can take "In order for" on "In."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.14,0:02:07.28,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,but instead you see a pale \Nmoon in the dawn sky
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.89,0:02:15.91,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,In order for us to find our way home,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.67,0:02:14.40,Chiha-card-TS,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}the plum blossoms still smell the same\Nwould I rather never seen her again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.53,0:02:21.71,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya doesn't know how to make adjustments \Nbased on which cards have been taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.42,0:02:24.65,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I reacted first...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.51,0:02:26.38,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.98,0:02:28.11,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't take the card...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.46,0:02:34.76,Chiha-title,A,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1500,0)}Chihaya Furu
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.03,0:03:44.03,Chiha-ep-title-verse,EpTitle,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(900,800)}Verse 7
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.03,0:03:44.03,Chiha-ep-title-poem,EpTitle,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(900,800)}But for \NAutumn's\N Coming
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.36,0:03:44.12,Chiha-main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.24,0:03:52.58,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,You're so good, Chihaya-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.89,0:03:53.85,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.85,0:03:55.99,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,I should have passed you the "I know" card,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.99,0:03:57.89,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,and then I should have waited before-
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.89,0:03:58.99,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya-chan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.38,0:04:00.66,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.66,0:04:01.95,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,She just fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.95,0:04:03.13,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,J-Just like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.51,0:04:10.41,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,She just bulls her way through a match \Nby relying on her fast reflex time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.41,0:04:11.63,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,and I still can't beat her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.43,0:04:14.22,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.94,0:04:17.60,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,In karuta, it refers to the speed
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.60,0:04:19.74,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,at which someone reacts to a card being read.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.16,0:04:21.32,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Some people say it's
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.32,0:04:24.20,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,the most important quality \Na karuta player can have.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.73,0:04:26.92,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,She was born with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.92,0:04:29.51,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya's karuta is driven \Nby that innate ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.16,0:04:33.10,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I don't have \Nanything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.10,0:04:33.96,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.21,0:04:36.47,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's actually possible \Nfor Chihaya-chan to play in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.47,0:04:39.46,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,the Queen match wearing \Na hakama from our store!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.46,0:04:41.21,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,On national TV!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.21,0:04:43.62,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think about this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.62,0:04:45.83,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Or would the violet one be better?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.46,0:04:45.83,Chiha-overlap,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.83,0:04:47.84,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,There are plenty of \Nbetter players in Class A.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.84,0:04:50.04,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,This one looks better,\N but I should choose this one
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.04,0:04:52.05,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,if I want people to understand\Nhow wonderful kimono are.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.05,0:04:53.95,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, this...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.36,0:04:55.48,Chiha-internaloverlap,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya and I are on completely different skill levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.65,0:05:00.73,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I have no interest in becoming a Master,\N so I don't mind losing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.39,0:05:02.30,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.87,0:05:05.21,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,If he were here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.30,0:05:16.68,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,If Chihaya were to practice \Nwith Arata instead of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.05,0:05:22.21,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,would she become a better player?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.52,0:05:28.43,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.48,0:05:31.87,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna go do some scouting!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.26,0:05:34.68,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Scouting?  For a fourth member?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.05,0:05:36.78,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,You have someone in mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.30,0:05:40.43,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,The second-smartest person in our \Ngrade, after Mashima Taichi,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.43,0:05:42.32,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Desktomu-kun, who happens to be in my class!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.32,0:05:43.28,Chiha-main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.37,0:05:46.32,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,You two can practice!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.93,0:05:50.14,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.70,0:05:54.33,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,We need five members before we \Ncan become an official club.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.91,0:06:06.69,Chiha-flashback,Em,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't have enough members, \Nyou can't be a club!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.43,0:06:09.68,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Two more to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.65,0:06:11.65,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm heading out then!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.65,0:06:13.05,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.05,0:06:14.12,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.03,0:06:23.52,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't he creep you out?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.52,0:06:25.37,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,School's over and he's still studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.80,0:06:26.81,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that Tsutomu-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.81,0:06:28.03,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,I mean Desktomu-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.33,0:06:31.41,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,He only leaves his desk \Nto go to the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:34.16,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't he look like a jelly bean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.80,0:06:43.53,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.35,0:06:46.92,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,There are too many judgmental fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.89,0:06:50.26,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, solved that problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.90,0:06:53.53,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,However, I like to study.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.01,0:06:57.39,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,The harder I work, the higher \Nour class's average scores are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.80,0:06:59.52,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,I'm willing to help out those fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.52,0:07:07.28,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,But it's kinda sad when he's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.28,0:07:09.78,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,glued to his desk all day and \Nonly second in our grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.03,0:07:11.03,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.44,0:07:12.92,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,When you put it that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.92,0:07:15.21,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Mashima-kun from Class 1 is really something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.21,0:07:17.79,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't study much, \Nyet he's top of the class!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.04,0:07:20.34,Chiha-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,I wish we could arrange a trade.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.34,0:07:23.79,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather have a number one stud \Nthan number two Desktomu-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.79,0:07:25.21,Chiha-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,I know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.21,0:07:26.65,Chiha-main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Is he upset?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.65,0:07:27.95,Chiha-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, no way...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.95,0:07:28.80,Chiha-main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.55,0:07:33.51,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Heya!  I'm Ayase Chihaya!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.51,0:07:35.43,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here to scout you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.43,0:07:38.39,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play karuta together \Nin the karuta club!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.52,0:07:41.39,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Consider this a bribe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.52,0:07:51.78,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Komano-kun.  You're the second-smartest \Nperson in our grade, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.20,0:07:56.33,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that karuta is a \Ngreat sport for smart people!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.33,0:07:58.58,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,If you join, we'll have four members
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.58,0:08:00.84,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and be one member closer to \Nbecoming an official club!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.84,0:08:02.71,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter if you \Ndon't have any experience!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.82,0:08:07.47,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.47,0:08:10.86,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, karuta as in Hundred Poets.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.86,0:08:12.76,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any point to playing karuta?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.62,0:08:15.51,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Can you become number one by playing karuta?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.39,0:08:18.67,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.36,0:08:21.86,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,There's no such thing as \Nprofessional karuta, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.15,0:08:24.37,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a game, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.37,0:08:25.40,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Why should I play this game?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.40,0:08:27.29,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Will it help me with my studies?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.29,0:08:28.77,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any benefit for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.01,0:08:33.67,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care about your excuses!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.67,0:08:37.53,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Stop griping and play a game!
